fg_segments: \ r \ r \ r \ r Privacy Policy \ r \ r You can access our web site home page and browse our site without disclosing your personal data.

Statistical information such as your IP address and which pages you have visited are collected for statistical purposes only. \ r UnitConversion.org uses "cookies" only to save your preferences such as the selected unit name so that on your next page visit this information can be used to restore the page to your last setting to provide you a personalized site experience whereever possible.

A "cookie" is an element of data which sometimes is sent to the user \ 's browser, which in turn, may store that element on the user \ 's hard drive or memory. \ r \ r Terms of Service \ r \ r You have permission to freely copy and use any generated code on personal and business web sites.
You do not have the right to sell, reproduce, or redistribute, parts of, or in its entirety, or as part of a derivative work, any of the code and/or scripts made available to you. \ r

While many efforts were made to ensure that all converter calculations are correct, UnitConversion.org makes no warranties, representations, or conditions, expressed or implied, regarding the use of the content of this web site.

In no event shall UnitConversion.org be held liable for any lost revenue, profits or other direct, indirect, special, incidental or consequential damages, data loss, loss of profits or any other kind of loss while using or misusing the contents of this web site. \ r Some unit definitions are based on Wikipedia(http://www.wikipedia.org), the free encyclopedia. \ r \ r \ r \ r We also use third party advertisements on unitconversion.org to support our site.

Some of these advertisers may use technology such as cookies and web beacons when they advertise on our site, which will also send these advertisers (such as Google through the Google AdSense program) information including your IP address, your ISP , the browser you used to visit our site, and in some cases, whether you have Flash installed.

This is generally used for geotargeting purposes (showing New York real estate ads to someone in New York, for example) or showing certain ads based on specific sites visited (such as showing cooking ads to someone who frequents cooking sites). \ r \ r DoubleClick DART cookies \ r We also may use DART cookies for ad serving through Google \ x92s DoubleClick, which places a cookie on your computer when you are browsing the web and visit a site using DoubleClick advertising (including some Google AdSense advertisements).
This cookie is used to serve ads specific to you and your interests ( \ x94interest based targeting \ x94).

The ads served will be targeted based on your previous browsing history (For example, if you have been viewing sites about visiting Las Vegas, you may see Las Vegas hotel advertisements when viewing a non-related site, such as on a site about hockey).
DART uses \ x93non personally identifiable information \ x94.
It does NOT track personal information about you, such as your name, email address, physical address, telephone number, social security numbers, bank account numbers or credit card numbers.

You can opt-out of this ad serving on all sites using this advertising by visiting http://www.doubleclick.com/privacy/dart_adserving.aspx \ r \ r You can choose to disable or selectively turn off our cookies or third-party cookies in your browser settings, or by managing preferences in programs such as Norton Internet Security.
However, this can affect how you are able to interact with our site as well as other websites.

This could include the inability to login to services or programs, such as logging into forums or accounts. \ r \ r Deleting cookies does not mean you are permanently opted out of any advertising program.
Unless you have settings that disallow cookies, the next time you visit a site running the advertisements, a new cookie will be added. \ r \ r \ r \ r \ r \ r
If you have any questions or concerns, feel free to contact us. \ r \ r \ r \ r \ r

raw_html:
Privacy Policy

You can access our web site home page and browse our site without disclosing your personal data. Statistical information such as your IP address and which pages you have visited are collected for statistical purposes only.
UnitConversion.org uses "cookies" only to save your preferences such as the selected unit name so that on your next page visit this information can be used to restore the page to your last setting to provide you a personalized site experience whereever possible. A "cookie" is an element of data which sometimes is sent to the user's browser, which in turn, may store that element on the user's hard drive or memory. 

Terms of Service

You have permission to freely copy and use any generated code on personal and business web sites. You do not have the right to sell, reproduce, or redistribute, parts of, or in its entirety, or as part of a derivative work, any of the code and/or scripts made available to you.
While many efforts were made to ensure that all converter calculations are correct, UnitConversion.org makes no warranties, representations, or conditions, expressed or implied, regarding the use of the content of this web site. In no event shall UnitConversion.org be held liable for any lost revenue, profits or other direct, indirect, special, incidental or consequential damages, data loss, loss of profits or any other kind of loss while using or misusing the contents of this web site. 
Some unit definitions are based on Wikipedia(http://www.wikipedia.org), the free encyclopedia.



We also use third party advertisements on unitconversion.org to support our site.  Some of these advertisers may use technology such as cookies and web beacons when they advertise on our site, which will also send these advertisers (such as Google through the Google AdSense program) information including your IP address, your ISP , the browser you used to visit our site, and in some cases, whether you have Flash installed.  This is generally used for geotargeting purposes (showing New York real estate ads to someone in New York, for example) or showing certain ads based on specific sites visited (such as showing cooking ads to someone who frequents cooking sites).

DoubleClick DART cookies
We also may use DART cookies for ad serving through Google\x92s DoubleClick, which places a cookie on your computer when you are browsing the web and visit a site using DoubleClick advertising (including some Google AdSense advertisements).  This cookie is used to serve ads specific to you and your interests (\x94interest based targeting\x94).  The ads served will be targeted based on your previous browsing history (For example, if you have been viewing sites about visiting Las Vegas, you may see Las Vegas hotel advertisements when viewing a non-related site, such as on a site about hockey).  DART uses \x93non personally identifiable information\x94.  It does NOT track personal information about you, such as your name, email address, physical address, telephone number, social security numbers, bank account numbers or credit card numbers.  You can opt-out of this ad serving on all sites using this advertising by visiting http://www.doubleclick.com/privacy/dart_adserving.aspx  

You can choose to disable or selectively turn off our cookies or third-party cookies in your browser settings, or by managing preferences in programs such as Norton Internet Security.  However, this can affect how you are able to interact with our site as well as other websites.  This could include the inability to login to services or programs, such as logging into forums or accounts.

Deleting cookies does not mean you are permanently opted out of any advertising program.  Unless you have settings that disallow cookies, the next time you visit a site running the advertisements, a new cookie will be added.





If you have any questions or concerns, feel free to contact us.
